  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Multiple sclerosis is often associated with pain. There is no standard treatment of this type
      of pain. Levetiracetam is a new anticonvulsant and it is the hypothesis that it could relieve
      central pain in multiple sclerosis. This is a randomised, double-blind, placebo-controlled,
      cross-over trial on the effect of levetiracetam 3000 mg daily on pain in multiple sclerosis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
